On Veterans Day, we honor the service and immense sacrifices of our nation’s veterans and their families. I was proud to help pass the PACT Act to expand access to VA health care and resources for toxic-exposed veterans. I’ll continue to support veterans across the Commonwealth.
Wishing a joyful Diwali to all those celebrating in Virginia and around the world!

So glad that a portion of the Coalfields Expressway is opening in Buchanan this week! I was proud to secure federal funding for the CFX, and I’m excited to see how it benefits the regional economy and helps Virginians get where they need to go.

Last week, I asked the Senate to confirm 364 promotions for servicemembers who are currently being denied the career advancement they’ve earned because of Sen. Tuberville’s military blockade. Tuberville objected. I will not forget about these Americans until they are confirmed.
